  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Improving production  inclusiveness and financial management practices towards sustainability</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">&lt;p style=&apos;margin-top:0in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:8.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal;font-size:15px;font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot; sans-serif;&apos;&gt;Twongerekawa Coko is a coffee cooperative which started in 2009  it is in Coko sector  Gakenke district in the northern part of Rwanda. The coop has 184 members and is sourcing its cherries from a total of 1306 farmers. In 2019 cooperative mobilized 30 young farmers. Different events aiming at involving more youth and women in coffee farming are expected. It is also anticipated to support the cooperative to develop external financial audit.&lt;/p&gt;</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">&lt;p&gt;Improving production  inclusiveness and financial management practices towards sustainability &lt;/p&gt;</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">&lt;p&gt;Project activities:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Support to mobilize youth to join coffee cooperative&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Mobilization of new members&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;External financial audit for the last 3 years( 2017-2019)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Developing strategic plan&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Dissemination of organic farming practices skills&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Agriterra services&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Business advisory services&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Female leadership training&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Follow up -Skills implementation on supervisory board training&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;Follow up -Skills implementation on organic coffee farming ToT&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Participating in agriculture show&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</narrative>
  </description>
